# Brand tokens and configuration

- Every visible company detail (name, legal name, tagline, contact, service areas, social) comes from `config/brand.ts`. Never hardcode brand strings in pages, components or data files.
- "Meridian Web Systems" is a temporary placeholder (D-05). Do not build final branding, logos or name-specific copy around it. Replacement happens only after the owner decision in `docs/business/FOUNDER-NAME-DECISION.md`.
- Visual identity is applied by swapping design-token values in the `@theme` block of `app/globals.css` and adjusting component classes — never by changing page structure, heading hierarchy, section order, metadata or routes. Procedure: `docs/prompts/18-visual-theme-development.md`; plan: `docs/brand/VISUAL-IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md`.
- Empty-string contact fields mean "hidden in UI" — keep that behaviour; do not invent placeholder phone numbers or emails.
- New colours must pass the contrast floors before being added as tokens (body ≥ 4.5:1, UI/large ≥ 3:1).
